10. What service and account name were used to retrieve files from the previous question? (service, username)
Let's pivot over to vsftpd.log, and we can see the bottom several lines:

Sun Apr 11 09:35:37 2021 [pid 8152] [ftp] OK LOGIN: Client "::ffff:192.168.10.5", anon password "?"
Sun Apr 11 09:35:45 2021 [pid 8154] [ftp] OK DOWNLOAD: Client "::ffff:192.168.10.5", "/www-data.bak", 2602 bytes, 544.81Kbyte/sec
Sun Apr 11 09:36:08 2021 [pid 8154] [ftp] OK DOWNLOAD: Client "::ffff:192.168.10.5", "/coupons_2013.md.bak", 131 bytes, 3.01Kbyte/sec

Well, we know from previous questions that the last two lines are showing the FTP (service!) transfer of the files we found earlier. Look at the first line, and we see it was an anonymous account that was logged into to perform this action.


11. What service and username were used to gain shell access to the server? (service, username)
In auth.log, we can see one line showing an accepted attempt:

Apr 11 09:41:19 thunt sshd[8260]: Accepted password for www-data from 192.168.10.5 port 40112 ssh2

Looking at the end of the line, we see it was attempted via SSH. Of course, the username used is the one the password was accepted for, which appears to be www-data.


And there we have it, our first completed CTF!

